# CI: verify lockfile on Linux before push

Title: **CI lockfile — verify Linux npm ci before every push**

The recurring CI failure on this repo is the **Install dependencies** stage
(`npm ci`) with:

```text
Missing: @emnapi/core@… from lock file
Missing: @emnapi/runtime@… from lock file
```

macOS `npm ci` can pass while Linux (GitHub Actions) fails. Local lint/test/build
is **not** enough.

## Mandatory pre-push

```bash
npm run verify:lockfile
npm run lint
npm run test
npm run build
```

## After any dependency change

1. Update deps as usual (`npm install …`).
2. If `verify:lockfile` fails, regenerate the lockfile with Linux Node 22:

```bash
docker run --rm -v "$PWD:/app" -w /app node:22-bookworm-slim \
  npm install --package-lock-only --ignore-scripts
```

3. Commit **both** `package.json` and `package-lock.json`.
4. Re-run `npm run verify:lockfile` until it prints OK.
5. Only then push / open the PR.
